{
  "texts": [
    "Importantly, these examples go beyond technical skills, such as mastering API syntax, and include the ability to reason about a given topic, and on the basis of new information.",
    "As the capabilities of LLMs in scientific contexts become more apparent, it has also become clear that further development does not depend solely on scaling LLMs during training (as in [24,25,26]).",
    "Jones' research [27] indicates that investing in Test Time (TT) computationallowing a fully trained model to generate a wider range of solutionshas proved remarkably effective: in the board game \"Go\" equal performance was achieved either by training a deep learning model for longer or by generating more solutions during TT.",
    "Cobe et al. [28] applied this approach to LLMs for solving mathematical text problems, showing that a smaller model using a TT strategy outperformed a 30 times larger model fine-tuned on task-specific data.",
    "Subsequently, Lightman et al. [29] highlighted the potential gains from more effective verifiers (the models that evaluate the TT-generated solutions)."
  ]
}